<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/891: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-10">December 10,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>824. Department received today your telegrams 1906 and 1910 of December 8,
                        together with your undated telegram which contained Foreign Office note in
                        regard to existence of state of war between the United States and Japan.</p>
                    <p>We hope that all goes well with you and your staff and other Americans in
                        Japan. Department has notified families of Embassy staff that you are all
                        safe and well.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>